ENTRY            A0849   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0849001   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 11         25
TITLE      Radioactive ion beam research made in Dubna.
AUTHOR     (G.M.Ter-Akopian,Yu.Ts.Oganessian,M.G.Itkis,
           G.G.Gulbekian,D.D.Bogdanov,A.S.Fomichev,M.S.Golovkov,
           A.M.Rodin,S.V.Stepantsov,R.Wolski)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,3POLIFJ)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,734,295,2004)
REL-REF    (O,D0218002,R.Wolski+,J,NP/A,701,29,2002) Cross
           sections obtained for the 8He + 4He elastic
           scattering were reported in D0218002.
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4ZZZDUB)the U-400M cyclotron of FLNR
           The selection of He-8 and He-6 ions was realized by
           double achromatic magnetic separator ACCULINNA
SAMPLE     Gas targets, filled to l-10 atm and cooled down to
           25-30 K, were used.
METHOD     (EDE,TOF)
INC-SOURCE The secondary beam of 8He was obtained via the
           bombardment of a beryllium target of a thickness of
           350 mg/cm2 by a 35 MeV/A primary beam of 11B.
DETECTOR   (MAGSP) The spectrometer ACCULINNA was used to separate
           8He from all other reaction products.
           (TELES,SI) delta-E-E telescopes made from highly
           granulated silicon detectors.
           (MWPC)
HISTORY    (20100402C) SB
           (20260205A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              25
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV/A
       26.0
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           32
SUBENT        A0849002   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                  5          9
REACTION   ((1-H-1(2-HE-8,T)2-HE-6,PAR,DA,RSD)=
           (2-HE-8(P,T)2-HE-6,PAR,DA))
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
LEVEL-PROP (2-HE-6,E-LVL=0.000,SPIN=0.,PARITY=+1.)
           (2-HE-6,E-LVL=1.797,SPIN=2.,PARITY=+1.)
STATUS     (CURVE,,G.M.Ter-Akopian+,J,NP/A,734,295,2004) Fig.2
HISTORY    (20260205A) SD: SF7=RSD added to nominator and
           SF7=RSD deleted from denominator in REACTION code.
           STATUS added.
ENDBIB               9
